tip.text: Yozu (citrus fruit) chicken soup ramen (980 yen): very clear soup and granular taste. Expect queue.
Nice food selection (DIY laksa for breakfast etc.) TWG teabags.

venue.name: Hong Kong International Airport (HKG) (香港國際機場)

tip.text: That chicken soup... Was really thick but tastes so good. The noodles are thin and nicely done. Let's forget about the calories count just for now...

venue.name: Tsukada Nojo 塚田農場 Japanese "Bijin Nabe" Restaurant

tip.text: Beef combo pho is not bad in the standards of restaurants in a mall. The bamboo straw looks legit.
6 different kinds of ramen in one shop! Chibakara ontama has a huge charsiu and generous serving with vegetables and garlic. For the meat lovers.
Tofu soup is tasty and quite spicy.
Nagoya style dry ramen is probably the signature and it comes with spicy shredded pork.
Grilled chicken here is probably at the higher end of what I could expect from a food stall.
Large room. A bit old (especially the look outside!) but still comfortable. Room keeping service somewhat needs improvement.
Small shio ramen shop, good for a bite at late night. Very thick (and fat) cubic pork.

venue.name: 喜多方ラーメン 坂内 有楽町店

tip.text: Quite a nice lounge. Spacious, comfortable, not crowded. Food is generally good too.

venue.name: Cathay Pacific Lounge (キャセイパシフィックラウンジ)

tip.text: Wifi password is now elementfresh. Brunch comes in good portion. Nice to sit outdoors though there isn't much view.

formattedAddress: 内堅947 (JR肥薩線 (えびの高原線))

tip.text: The rice and the mutton seems to be their signature. The mutton was OK, the rice was just fine. Good try for first-timers.
Typical HK hot pot. Not too bad in HK standards though. Seafood here served in pot is good.
Black King ramen with soft egg. Try with more garlic.

formattedAddress: Shop 4, G/F, V Point (2-22 Tang Lung Street)

tip.text: Ngau Nam (beef) sandwich came in rather small size but is juicy and delicious. Lennon fries as sides is a nice choice. Come if you are not starving! Not crowded at night.
Good for a quick lunch. A bit salty for my smoked salmon penne.
Beef noodles was fine. The "three small dishes" appetizer was not impressive. Fortunately service was okay at 6pm. Not worth for queuing long but a good choice for a quick meal.

location.address: Shop A, 6/F, Causeway Bay Plaza 1, 489 Hennessy Rd
formattedAddress: Shop A, 6/F, Causeway Bay Plaza 1, 489 Hennessy Rd

tip.text: Spicy pot comes in large portion and rich ingredients. Authentically spicy. Other Beijing dishes are not outstanding but generally good in HK standard.

formattedAddress: G/F, Hundred City Centre, 7-17 Amoy St

tip.text: Being green and healthy is a plus. Yet the Onsen Tamago (egg benedict) was served cold... Not even the matcha was hot. Slightly overpriced for its average food quality.
Lunch set bento went beyond expectation. Grilled codfish was mediocre and not worth the price.
Interesting combination of hot pot and barbecue with the steamboat. Ask for a smaller portion if you come alone.
Probably one of the only restaurant still open at late hours. Nice garlic seafood rice, not too spicy.
Must try espresso and pandan pancake. Far beyond expectation.
